properties.areaDesc: West Slopes North Central Cascades and Passes
properties.headline: Winter Weather Advisory issued January 8 at 12:41AM PST until January 8 at 4:00AM PST by NWS Seattle WA
properties.description:
* WHAT...Snow continued above 3000 feet. Additional snow
accumulations of 2 to 4 inches.

* WHERE...Cascade mountains and valleys of Snohomish and King
Counties, including Darrington, Index, Skykomish, Stevens
Pass, and Snoqualmie Pass.

* WHEN...Until 4 AM PST early this morning.

* IMPACTS...Plan on slippery road conditions.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...Snow is expected at elevations above 3000
feet through early Wednesday morning. The Northwest Avalanche
Center expects high avalanche danger to continue through through
Wednesday. Check nwac.us for the latest avalanche conditions.
properties.instruction:
Slow down and use caution while traveling.

For the latest road conditions in Washington state, call 5 1 1.

NWSheadline: WINTER WEATHER ADVISORY REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 4 AM PST EARLY THIS MORNING ABOVE 3000 FEET
